                <note type="abstract">A very inadequate, idiosyncratic edition and English translation of Yefet’s Judaeo-Arabic translation and commentary on Song of Songs, based on only one, complete—albeit rather late (17th-century)—Ms. in the Bibliothèque nationale. No mention at all is made of the several other Mss. witnesses in G. Tamani’s preliminary inventory, nor is any use made of the extremely important British Library Ms. Or. 2554, written in Arabic characters and during Yefet’s lifetime, and unquestionably preserving a much more original text of Yefet’s work (see, inter alios, Ben-Shammai’s seminal article on this matter in Alei Sefer [1976], as well as Wechsler’s 2008 edition of Yefet, pp. 97–112, 144–48). See also the review of K. Almbladh in Orientalia Suecana 59 (2010): 217–18.</note>
